        "content": "**Network-level observability**: Beckn API spans, audit logs, and HTTP request metrics from the network pipeline.\n\n**Metric path**: Onix adapter emits `onix_http_request_count` via OTLP. BAP/BPP collectors filter and forward it to the network collector, which exposes it as `onix_network_onix_http_request_count_total` on Prometheus (namespace `onix_network`). All panels query `job=\"otel-collector-network\"` to isolate network-level data.\n\n**No data?** 1) Ensure the observability stack is running: `docker compose up -d`. 2) Send requests through the Onix adapter to generate metrics. 3) Use [Zipkin UI](http://localhost:9411) for traces. 4) In Grafana Explore (Loki), try `{service_name=~\".+\"}` to see all logs.",
